    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive outlook, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (80.29) and **Christian Yelich** (75.84). **Yordan Alvarez** remains our premier start, leveraging a superior xwOBA profile and a favorable matchup against Emerson Hancock. Similarly, **Christian Yelich** earns a high grade due to a strong SP skill advantage and a prime spot in the #3 hole. While **Junior Caminero** (73.34) carries a slightly lower projection, his massive +19% boost from Luis Gil\u2019s high xERA makes him an essential start. We are particularly monitoring the potential for stolen bases from **Hyeseong Kim** (61.59); his aggressive jump against the slower delivery of Kumar Rocker provides a rare categorical edge in the scarce SB department, despite the risk inherent in his #8 batting position.\n\nOur lineup construction faces tough decisions at the margins, most notably with **Josh Smith** (52.05), who was the first cut from the active roster. While **Josh Smith** benefits from a positive platoon advantage against Tyler Glasnow, his projected #8 spot in the order ultimately suppressed his utility relative to the higher-floor production of **Caleb Durbin** (56.28). Meanwhile, **Victor Scott II** (34.48) remains firmly on the bench; despite his elite speed, he is currently buried at the #9 spot against an elite arm in Connelly Early, making him a liability in both efficiency and category upside today.\n\nManagers should proceed with caution regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all starters. Players like **Dillon Dingler** (48.96) and **Colt Keith** (68.51) are currently positioned for strong matchups, but any deviation from the projected lineup slots could significantly alter their daily efficiency. Specifically, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (66.10) provides a dual-threat profile, but owners must be wary of the \"Wind In\" warning at his venue, which threatens to dampen his power output despite a solid platoon edge against Carmen Mlodzinski. We will continue to monitor the status of **Trea Turner** (63.68), **Kyle Schwarber** (60.47), **Kazuma Okamoto** (59.00), and **Jerar Encarnacion** (53.25) as the final confirmed lineups are posted to ensure our game caps are deployed with maximum surgical precision.",
